<P>
   KOSOVO-MAIN _ TIRANA, Albania _ Humanitarian aid is being rushed
to ethnic Albanian refugees as NATO and the Clinton administration
are put on the defensive about why they didn't anticipate the scope
of the problem and preposition food and supplies. Meanwhile, plans
are afoot to airlift more than 100,000 refugees out of the region.
Most will go elsewhere in Europe while a few thousand will come to
the United States. (Roughton, Cox News Service) 20.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-CLEANSE _ ROZAJE, Montenegro, Yugoslavia _ Although
difficult to independently verify, first person accounts by
refugees offer strikingly similar accounts of the unspeakable evil
unleashed upon fleeing Kosovar Albanians by Serb troops, police and
paramilitary units. Using spy planes, satellites and unmanned
drones equipped with high altitude cameras, NATO is beginning to
document the claims of the escaping refugees (Holmes/Deans, Cox
News Service) 25.
