Serbian capital. By Steven Erlanger.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-ALBANIA (Tirana) _ At its starkest, the truth in Kosovo
is simple. Serbs, enboldened or maddened by NATO bombings, are on a
rampage of ethnic cleansing that has caused nearly a quarter of the
ethnic Albanian population to flee. But close up, real life is
rarely simple. Between those deaths lies a tangled web of history,
friendships and enmities, of war and routine business that were
echoed all over Kosovo. And those are the minutae of life and death
that are drowned out by the clashing statements of Washington and
Belgrade. By Alessandra Stanley.
