  (lb) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Treasury's schedule of financing this week offers Monday's
regular weekly auction of three- and six-month bills and a sale on
Tuesday of $7 billion of 30-year Treasury inflation-indexed
securities.
</P>
<P>
   By the close of the New York cash market on Friday, traders
said, the rate on the outstanding three-month bill was 4.28 percent
and a six-month bill was 4.30 percent.
