BBN-BROWN (Los Angeles) _ Some have called it a doomsday signal.
Some say it was the perfect move for the team. However you feel
about the signing of Kevin Brown, know this: It was the biggest
deal of baseball's offseason ($105 million, to be exact) and it
signaled the return of the Los Angeles Dodgers as major players. A
look at what makes Brown so attractive and why the Dodgers had to
have him. 
By Brian Dohn. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
