<P>
   LA-GANGKID (Los Angeles) _ The black R.I.P. tattoo crudely inked
into the neck of 11-year-old Robert Lomas is the first sign the
youngest member of the notorious Langdon Street Gang has grown up
around killing, death and pain. In death, Robert has literally
become the poster child for Los Angeles City Attorney James Hahn's
war against gangs in North Hills. By Greg Gittrich. (Will move in
``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   SCHOOL-DIET (Los Angeles) _ Staring at a half-eaten heap of
chicken nuggets, Byrd Middle School student Deisy Murillo is on the
front line of the school district's battle for the minds and
stomachs of students. Under a federal order to cut fat and boost
nutrition, the Los Angeles Unified School District and other school
systems are engaged in a daily struggle to balance what students
think is good food and what food that is good of them. By David R.
Baker. (Will move in ``a'' national and ``n'' California news
files.)
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-BOX-OFFICE (Los Angeles) _ ``The Matrix,'' a futuristic
action movie starring Keanu Reeves, has won the weekend box office
battle. By Dave McNary. (Will move in ``a'' national and ``n''
California news files.)
</P>
