<SLUG> BC-TORNADO-AFTERMATH-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
RESCUE CREWS HUNT FOR SURVIVORS OF DEADLY TORNADO 
</HEADLINE>
  (lb) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BENTON, La. _ Emergency crews searched on Sunday through the
rubble left by a tornado that devastated this small town on
Saturday, while survivors remembered the dead and injured at Easter
services.
</P>
<P>
   By afternoon, the authorities reported finding no more bodies,
leaving the death toll at six, with more than 100 people injured
and 200 forced from their homes.
</P>
<P>
   Eight twisters were reported in northwestern Louisiana on
Saturday afternoon. But the one that hit Benton, about 10 miles
north of Shreveport, did by far the most damage, practically
destroying two mobile-home parks and a subdivision and causing the
only deaths.
</P>
<P>
   Law-enforcement officials blocked two of the three affected
residential areas on Sunday afternoon, allowing those who lived
there to enter only to check on the damage.
</P>
<P>
   At one mobile-home park, called Haymeadow, homes were splintered
and twisted unrecognizably.
</P>
<P>
   The skies were heavy with heat and humidity, and residents were
still without power in several parts of town. Power lines knocked
down by the high winds and flying debris were being replaced as
quickly as possible by Southwestern Electric Power Co., while other
emergency crews removed rubble and debris.
</P>
<P>
   Residents of this town of 2,500 huddled together, but many
refused to speak with reporters. Shock was visible on the faces of
many.
</P>
<P>
   Church services with special Easter sermons were held, and
worshippers gathered to pay tribute to those who had lost their
lives and homes.
</P>
<P>
   Power was on in downtown Benton, so convenience and grocery
stores continued operating.
</P>
<P>
   A couple from Canada, who refused to give their names, took
refuge in their trailer when the storms hit. The woman said they
hooked the trailer down and prayed that it would be heavy enough to
withstand the winds.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
