DRUGDEATHS (PHOENIX ) The wires hung from windows, walls and
ceiling were supposed to look like booby traps set to snare any
would-be thieves. But the decoys didn't stop a gunman from shooting
three people to death Sunday inside the apartment. Andrew Parks,
37, and his sister, Shelly Parks, 33, died in the living room of
the apartment in the 400 block of West Osborn Road, police said. A
third man, whom police did not identify, was found shot to death in
a back bedroom. By RICHARD RUELAS. Story will move in the `A'
